{"hadithnumber": "126", "text": "I saw Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) leaning on a cushion on his left side.”"}
{"hadithnumber": "127", "text": "“Allah’s Messenger said (Allah bless him and give him peace): ‘Should I tell you about the greatest of the major sins?’ They said: ‘Yes indeed, O Messenger of Allah!’ He said: ‘Associating partners with Allah, and recalcitrance against parents.’ Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) sat down, and he was leaning on a support. He added: '...and false testimony’ or: ‘false speech.’ Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) went on speaking until we said: ‘If only he would keep silent!”"}
{"hadithnumber": "128", "text": "Allah’s Messenger said (Allah bless him and give him peace):‘As for me, I do not eat while leaning on a support!’”"}
{"hadithnumber": "129", "text": "Allah’s Messenger said (Allah bless him and give him peace): 'I do not eat while leaning on a support! I do not eat while leaning on a support'!”"}
{"hadithnumber": "130", "text": "I saw Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) leaning on a cushion.”"}
